cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.IT

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language syntax parsing and production. It may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as the software model, SP61, embodies ICMAUS concepts which involve multiple alignment, unification, and search. Additionally, the paper may belong to cs.SD (Sound) as it deals with the representation of natural language in a simple format. Finally, it may belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) as the ICMAUS framework involves information compression.
